      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "b93ededbf63e176a",
        "text": "We can then call the observation results of this coupling by feedback illegalities, i.e. forms in the medium of illegality. The loosely coupled elements of illegalizing observation would then be mutually exclusive formal expectations and illegal coupling possibilities. The self-exclusion of these expectations, however, only becomes observable in such a way that they are coupled to illegal forms and thereby re-enclosed - under the structure-protecting condition that this must not become known."
      },
      "date": 1655890608908
