      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "166b8a93e84ef31b",
        "text": "The modalization effect of the medium can then be seen in the fact that illegality enables the coupleability of otherwise non-coupleable (because formally mutually exclusive) elements into forms, and makes illegality available to society by fulfilling formal expectations through its violation. Accordingly, in illegality we are dealing with two degrees of order of violating: with the violation of expectations by an observer who, contrary to expectations, encounters legal-political indifferences and from there concludes that the structures he observes have been violated and, thus, that there is a medium of illegality."
